of that, all the demography.

00:42:19.400 --> 00:42:23.015
Age, education.

00:42:23.015 --> 00:42:25.000
Yeah.

00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:30.550
So in answer to your
question, we'll see what the--

00:42:30.550 --> 00:42:32.520
that among some of
these poor people,

00:42:32.520 --> 00:42:35.450
they have a very high return on
assets, real physical assets,

00:42:35.450 --> 00:42:37.450
and we'll see where they're
putting their money.

00:42:41.970 --> 00:42:45.470
So inequalities going
down in some sense, right?

00:42:45.470 --> 00:42:49.160
So anyway, this is not the
story of a poverty trap.

00:42:51.710 --> 00:42:54.020
Now I'm not claiming
